  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Addressing unmet essential  health needs of conflict-affected IDP populations in Borno State.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project- &quot;Addressing unmet essential health needs of conflict-affected IDP populations in Borno State&quot; is a six-months project aimed at ensuring a continuity in the provision of essential secondary and tertiary health services to conflict-affected people across three local government areas of Borno State (Maiduguri, Jere and Monguno LGAs) through Strengthening of referral pathways/mechanisms and medical evacuation of patients/injured from primary to secondary levels of health care, including payments for treatment in hospitals, whilst also strengthening diseases surveillance and outbreak response through health Rapid Response Teams (RRT).</narrative>
  </description>
